td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Is there REALLY a future for MAs?</span><hr size=1> I have a 60 MA that I am quite fond of.  He is my first AO char and I have had a blast with him so far.  I know I have not spent wisely on the IP him being my first character and all so i look forward to 14.2.  I mostly soloed through my first 50 levels and I thought I was actually doing ok.  Recently, I have been teaming alot more and I cant believe the difference in other classes compared to the MA.  I am out the other night with an agent, a fixer, an enforcer and an adventurer - all high 50's very low 60's.  As we get farther and farther along I find myself pretty much in the role of the team doctor since I was doing little to no damage compared to the other classes and I couldnt take the hits if I did gain the red agro.  The team certainly did like my crit buff and healing though.  I expected the enforcer to be the meat on the mission but it turns out the fixer was the power house critting for 2500 a pop every 3-4 hits.  I saw him drop a red in two shots!! No help.  My crit is only 350's at best and I never get the crit rate that others seem to get with my buffs.  Others seems to hit on average just as fast as I do with regular attacks and average much higher damage.  Im not complaining here, what I am looking for is some hope that i can look forward to the advertised damage over time actually taking effect in the future and that I am not going to have to continue to be a second rate doctor in a group (considering that they will nerf any other reason anyone would want an MA in a group = crit buff).  Anyone have good news? <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/uantyx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Antyx</A> at: 5/2/02 7:01:48 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=keldrys>Keldrys</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Peking Duck</span><br>  Posts: 141<br> <font color=#660000>(5/2/02 8:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1918.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> Fear not, Antyx, the future is quite bright for MAs =)  14.2 is gonna create massive changes in gameplay that will eliminate most of what you've described (overequipping).  The reason that the other people you were grouped with is most likely because they were twinks of higher level characters.  They can afford to spend the time (and have the knowledge and resources) to massively overequip their characters.  MAs are an excellent class to play and after 14.2 will be even more powerful in comparison to most other classes.  <br>
<br>
My best advice would be to get in the best possible implants that you can.  They are quite expensive and take awhile to build correctly but the effects are quite significant.  Everyone's first character gets screwed up.  My first was an enforcer with points in swimming, adventuring, pistol, MA, used protector squibbers (piercing) until level 63 before switching to rider executioners, etc.<br>
<br>
MAs will be the best damage dealers over time after 14.2 and are very good at soloing (I still do at 182).  Everyone else, on the other hand, will now be subject to overequipping rules and have much much lower chance to crit. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/udespore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>despore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#660000>(5/3/02 2:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1918.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> i noticed this to, at lower lvl's ma's rock for dmg, but then once we get higher, people start mad over equiping, and their dmg sky rockets vs ours.   it gets worst at the low 100's=/ when people start using ql 200 weaponry.   and the only way you can od more dmg is buffs, or implants (which theycan do to)  however at 150 now, i've noticed i'm catching up in dmg!, and contributing more then being a portable crit buff generator=p <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=1918.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showNextMessage?topicID=1918.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1918.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.emailToFriend?topicID=1918.topic><img src=http://